      "content": "65-75% is way too vague for them. they're looking for a \"go\" or \"no-go\" decision here. if you're saying there's a 75% chance of disruptive change, that's basically a red flag. can you actually pin it down? if you look at the most recent troop movements and logistics reports, is there a reason you can't push that confidence up to a \"High Confidence\" rating for stability? they need to know if they can trust the current status quo to hold for the next six months.",
